org.letras.psi.semantic
Interface ISegmenter

All Known Implementing Classes:
SimpleSegmenter
public interface ISegmenter

An ISegmenter is a service that segments pen input based on configurable heuristics. The segments can then be further processed into other components. This is the client-side interface for the segmenter, which only provides facilities for adjusting the heuristics model and for retrieving the interface ISegmentationProvider that is exposed to the actual ISemanticService that process the segmented data.

Author:
Jannik Jochem
